@startuml app_shutdown_sequence
' Created 2026-05-13: per claudeit/_diagram_amendments.md
!include dark-theme.puml
title App shutdown / dispose sequence\nSix paths; Wave 1 fixes applied (annotated inline)

participant "User /\nTray exit" as USER
participant "Win32 /\nSessionEnding" as WIN
participant App as APP
participant CrashHandler as CRASH
participant "Single-instance\nWatcher" as WATCH
participant "BrightnessFlyout\n+ Settings*" as UI
participant ProfileManager as PM
participant EnvironmentalCurveService as ECS
participant MonitorService as MS
participant DDCRecoveryService as DRS
participant TrayIconManager as TIM
participant KnownDisplaysStore as KDS
participant ShellNotifyIcon as SNI
participant AppSettings as APS

== Path A: user-initiated exit (tray menu / hotkey) ==
USER -> APP : ExitApplication()
APP -> APP : Mouse.Capture(null) released before teardown\n(no longer drops MouseUp commit)
APP -> UI  : SettingsWindow.OnClosing flushes curve debounce
APP -> PM  : SaveOnShutdown (post-H-13 fix; profile state flushed)
APP -> UI  : OnFlyoutClosed -> release 7 ctor subscriptions\n+ CancelPreviewSweep (post-H-18 / H-19 fixes)
APP -> ECS : Dispose (called from OnFlyoutClosed; post-H-14 fix)
APP -> MS  : Dispose -> _writeThrottler drain, _entries clear
MS  -> KDS : Flush() then Dispose -> _stampDebounceTimer disposed\n(post-H-15 fix)
APP -> DRS : Dispose -> cancel fallback worker\nunsubscribe MonitorsRefreshed
APP -> TIM : Dispose -> _renderer cleanup
APP -> SNI : Dispose -> NIM_DELETE
APP -> APS : Save (atomic temp+rename, post-M-04 fix)
APP -> APP : Process.Exit

== Path B: watcher-orphan restart ==
WATCH -> APP : detect child crash (exit code not in UserExitCodes)
WATCH -> WATCH : spawn replacement
note right
  CrashHandler.Environment.Exit(1) is still in UserExitCodes for
  graceful exits, but UnhandledException now flows through Path C
  with a distinct exit code so the watcher CAN restart on crashes.
end note

== Path C: UI thread unhandled exception ==
APP -> CRASH : OnUnhandledException(args)
CRASH -> CRASH : log + Environment.Exit (non-user code)
note right
  Exit code 1 removed from CrashHandler.UserExitCodes (post-M-13 fix).
  Watcher now restarts the process on unhandled UI-thread exceptions.
end note

== Path D: background thread exception ==
note over APP
  Threading.Timer callbacks now wrapped in try/catch
  (NightLightRegistry.OnResendTimerFired,
   NightLightSettingsHandler.OnDeferredRegistryTimerFired)
  post-M-11 fix. Background timer faults no longer tear down
  the process; the exception is logged and swallowed.
end note

== Path E: SessionEnding (logoff / shutdown) ==
WIN -> APP : SessionEnding event
APP -> APP : _sessionEnding = true (re-entry guard)
APP -> APP : ExitApplication() (post-H-17 fix)
note right
  Path E now flows through Path A:
   - NIM_DELETE fires -> no ghost tray icon.
   - Hotkeys unregistered.
   - KnownDisplays flushed.
  The _sessionEnding guard prevents reentry if both
  WM_QUERYENDSESSION and WM_ENDSESSION fire.
end note

== Path F: taskkill ==
note over APP
  SIGKILL-equivalent. No graceful path.
  AppSettings.Save and ProfileManager.Save now use atomic
  temp+rename (post-M-04 fix), so a mid-write taskkill leaves
  the previous valid file intact instead of a zero-byte stub.
  KnownDisplaysStore writes are still best-effort.
end note

@enduml
